paragraphs.title: Convert CSV-based DataFrame into TaggedItems
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.sql.Row
import com.advancedspark.ml.TaggedItem
import org.apache.spark.sql.functions._

val itemsWithTagsDF = itemsDF.select($"id", $"title", $"tags").map(row => {
  val id = row.getInt(0)
  val title = row.getString(1)
  val tags = row.getString(2).trim.split("\\|")
  TaggedItem(id, title, tags)
}).toDF("itemId", "title", "tags")
.as("itemsWithTags")

itemsWithTagsDF.registerTempTable("itemsWithTags")
val itemsWithExplodedTagsDF = sqlContext.sql("SELECT itemId, title, explode(tags) as tag FROM itemsWithTags") 

z.show(itemsWithExplodedTagsDF)

paragraphs.title: Convert Tag Strings to Indexes
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.StringIndexer

val tagIndexer = new StringIndexer()
  .setInputCol("tag")
  .setOutputCol("tagIndex")

paragraphs.title: One-Hot Encode the Tag Indexes Into binary vectors
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.feature.OneHotEncoder

val oneHotEncoder = new OneHotEncoder()
  .setInputCol(tagIndexer.getOutputCol)
  .setOutputCol("tagsOneHotEncoded")
  .setDropLast(false)

paragraphs.title: Transform Features Using Pipeline
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.Pipeline

val pipeline = new Pipeline()
  .setStages(Array(tagIndexer, oneHotEncoder))
  
val pipelineModel = pipeline.fit(itemsWithExplodedTagsDF)
val resultsDF = pipelineModel.transform(itemsWithExplodedTagsDF)
z.show(resultsDF.select("*").sort($"itemId" asc))

paragraphs.title: Combine One-Hot Encoded Tag Vectors for each Item
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.mllib.linalg.SparseVector
import org.apache.spark.mllib.linalg.Vectors
import org.jblas.DoubleMatrix

val itemsWithTagsOneHotEncodedCombinedDF = resultsDF.map{ 
  case Row(itemId: Long, title: String, tag: String, tagIndex: Double, tagsOneHotEncoded: SparseVector) => 
    (itemId, (new DoubleMatrix(tagsOneHotEncoded.toDense.values)))
  }.reduceByKey((tagsOneHotEncodedDoubleMatrix1, tagsOneHotEncodedDoubleMatrix2) => 
    tagsOneHotEncodedDoubleMatrix1.ori(tagsOneHotEncodedDoubleMatrix2)
  ).mapValues(tagsOneHotEncodedDoubleMatrixCombined => Vectors.dense(tagsOneHotEncodedDoubleMatrixCombined.toArray))
  .toDF("itemId", "tagsOneHotEncodedCombined").as("oneHotEncodedCombined")

val joinedResultsWithTagsOneHotEncodedCombinedDF = itemsWithTagsDF
  .join(itemsWithTagsOneHotEncodedCombinedDF, $"itemsWithTags.itemId" === $"oneHotEncodedCombined.itemId")

z.show(joinedResultsWithTagsOneHotEncodedCombinedDF
  .select($"itemsWithTags.itemId", $"title", $"tags", $"tagsOneHotEncodedCombined").sort($"itemId" asc))

paragraphs.title: Use Cross Validation to Find best k-means Cluster model Based on WSSSE
paragraphs.text:
import org.apache.spark.ml.clustering.KMeans

val kmeans = new KMeans()
  .setFeaturesCol("tagsOneHotEncodedCombined")
  .setPredictionCol("clusterId")

val possibleNumClusters = Seq(5, 10, 15)
val possibleMaxIterations = Seq(15, 20, 25)

val results = 
  for { 
    numClusters <- possibleNumClusters
    maxIterations <- possibleMaxIterations
  } yield {
      kmeans.setK(numClusters)
      kmeans.setMaxIter(maxIterations)
      val kmeansModel = kmeans.fit(joinedResultsWithTagsOneHotEncodedCombinedDF)
      val WSSSE = kmeansModel.computeCost(joinedResultsWithTagsOneHotEncodedCombinedDF)
      (WSSSE, numClusters, maxIterations, kmeansModel)
  }
  
val (bestWSSSE, bestNumClusters, bestMaxIterations, bestKMeansModel) = results.sortBy(_._1).toSeq(0)
